sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K577900
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A reporter plasmid using pCAt as a constitutive promoter in front of a BFP gene. Within 24 hours, cells should fluoresce blue.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyle Jones
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The composite part K156026 containing B0034+K156010 is combined as a suffix insertion to the pCat backbone.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K156026
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This composite part is made of a strong, standard ribosomal binding site and a part that codes for blue fluorescent protein, which can be used as a reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: George McArthur IV

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Cat
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vikram Vijayan, Allen Hsu, Lawrence Fomundam

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SBFP2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for orange fluorescent protein (OFP). Fluorescent proteins are useful tools for visualizing and quantifying protein expression in cells. OFP is yet another fluorescent protein, like GFP, that can be utilized as a reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: George McArthur IV
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: OFP was cloned from the tentacles of ''Cerianthus'' sp., a tube anemone. The original sequence was obtained from GenBank (VERSION AY296063.1, GI:31616578).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was codon-optimized for expression in ''E. coli''. The following restriction enzyme sites were also removed: EcoRI, NotI, XbaI, SpeI, PstI, NheI, AvrII, ApoI, MfeI, NsiI, SbfI.
